---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Privacy Policy | Grammarly AI Humanizer" 
  description="Read the Grammarly AI Humanizer privacy policy. Understand how we protect your text input confidentiality, process data, and guarantee secure, private AI humanization."
  canonicalUrl="https://grammarlyaihumanizer.com/privacy-policy/"
>
  <Header />
  
  <main class="flex-grow relative py-20 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <!-- Floating Mesh Background -->
    <div class="mesh-backdrop"></div>
    
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl relative z-10">
      <!-- Page Header -->
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <span class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-link mb-3 inline-block">Legal Framework</span>
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-[-1px] text-ink mb-4">
          Privacy Policy
        </h1>
        <p class="text-mute text-xs font-mono">Effective Date: July 2, 2026</p>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Content Card -->
      <div class="card-marketing-large bg-canvas border border-hairline p-8 sm:p-12 rounded-lg shadow-sm space-y-8 text-body text-sm leading-relaxed">
        
        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink">1. Introduction</h2>
          <p>
            Welcome to <strong>Grammarly AI Humanizer</strong> ("we," "our," or "us"). We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring a secure experience when you use our undetectable AI humanizer engine. This Privacy Policy describes how we handle, process, and protect your information when you interact with our website and services.
          </p>
          <p>
            By using our website, you agree to the practices outlined in this policy. If you do not agree with any terms, please do not use our services.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink">2. Text Processing and Confidentiality</h2>
          <p>
            The core feature of Grammarly AI Humanizer is transforming AI-generated content into high-quality, human-like text. Here is how we safeguard your input text:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
            <li>
              <strong>No Permanent Storage of Input/Output:</strong> The text you paste into our editor and the humanized results generated by our system are processed in real-time. We do not store your original or humanized text permanently on our servers.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>No Model Training:</strong> We do not use the text you submit to train, fine-tune, or improve our AI models or third-party Large Language Models (LLMs). Your intellectual property remains entirely yours.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Secure APIs:</strong> Text humanization requests are transmitted over secure, encrypted channels (HTTPS) to our backend APIs, which run isolated translation passes to output humanized text.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink">3. Information We Collect</h2>
          <p>
            To maintain service security, prevent abuse, and optimize our user experience, we collect limited non-identifying data:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
            <li>
              <strong>Usage Data:</strong> We collect basic metadata about your visits, such as IP addresses (anonymized), browser types, referring pages, timestamps, and page interaction data.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>API Logs:</strong> Temporal operational logs are generated during text processing to handle rate limiting and prevent abuse (e.g., automated scraping). These logs are automatically pruned after 24 hours.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Cookies:</strong> We use essential cookies to save your settings, such as your light/dark theme preference, and to support analytics tools that measure traffic patterns.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink">4. How We Use Information</h2>
          <p>
            We use the limited data we collect to:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
            <li>Provide, maintain, and monitor the stability of the Grammarly AI Humanizer tool.</li>
            <li>Prevent spam, security exploits, and violate fair-use policies.</li>
            <li>Understand general user navigation trends to improve the user interface and overall performance.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink">5. Third-Party Services</h2>
          <p>
            We may use third-party tools to assist in service delivery, such as:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
            <li>
              <strong>Analytics Providers:</strong> We use privacy-compliant web analytics (like Google Analytics with IP anonymization) to compile aggregated traffic reports.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Hosting & Infrastructure:</strong> Our platform is hosted on secure cloud providers with enterprise-grade data security protocols.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            These third parties only have access to information necessary to perform their services and are contractually prohibited from using or sharing it for other purposes.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink">6. Data Security</h2>
          <p>
            We employ robust administrative, technical, and physical security measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. However, please remember that no transmission over the Internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink">7. GDPR and CCPA Compliance</h2>
          <p>
            Depending on your location, you may have specific data protection rights, including the right to access, rectify, or delete any limited personal data we hold. Since we do not require account registration or store submitted text, the amount of personal data we retain is minimal or non-existent. For inquiries regarding your rights, please reach out via our contact page.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink">8. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
          <p>
            We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated "Effective Date." We encourage you to review this page periodically to stay informed about how we protect your privacy.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink">9. Contact Us</h2>
          <p>
            If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please visit our <a href="/contact-us/" class="text-link hover:underline font-medium">Contact Us</a> page or email us at devilfake8c@gmail.com.
          </p>
        </section>

      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  
  <Footer />
</Layout>
